Equation: Vi=Si+D (Equation 3.1 in reference). The diagonal terms in Vi indicate that the total variability affecting the summary measures in each study is the sum of the within-study variance and the between-study variance. Similarly, the off-diagonal terms in Vi indicate that the total covariance that is contributed by each study is the sum of the within-study covariance and the between-study covariance. Equations (2.2) and (2.3) show that the total variance and total covariance are both important in the estimation of the pooled effects and their precision.
